subSubSection.paragraph:
Mature larva: Sternal spatula bilobed, the anterior free portion slightly wider than the posterior portion (
Kieffer 1889
). Two groups of lateral papillae present on each side of the spatula, each group of 2 setose and 1 asetose papillae. Terminal segment with 6 setose and 2 corniform terminal papillae (

Moehn
1955

).

Widespread Europe, Algeria and Kazakhstan (
Gagne and Jaschhof 2017
).
